Security Operations Fundamentals > [T2]: Lab - Nessus: Detect Log4Shell

Detect CVE-2021-44228 vulnerability (Log4Shell)

Your VM has a vulnerable docker container to the Log4shell famous bug. Nessus can detect this in multiple ways, one way is via credentials scan or web application scan (I will leave this for you to play with), but our focus will be on the pre-defined template from Nessus.

To do this, open up your browser and visit https://127.0.0.1:8443.

Hit the New Scan button, choose the Log4Shell Remote Checks template, add the details, and click Save.

Place 127.0.0.1 as your target address.


As we have done earlier, launch the scan from the My Scans folder.

This type of scan should not take much time, and the result will be similar to the screenshot below.
 


Switching to the Vulnerabilities tab, you will see that Nessus identified one critical vulnerability with the target host.


You can drill down into the vulnerabilities by clicking on any of them. Nessus will provide a detailed description of the finding along with the risk information and, most notably, a solution to mitigate the security vulnerability.
